Subject: BUG: parameter editor not updated properly when dealing with dirty model
Date: Sat, 23 Aug 2008 04:12:30 -0600
X-Mailer: Apple Mail (2.926)

When save and run is selected, it checks if the SBML/GCM model  
associated with the analysis view is dirty.  If it is, it ask if you  
wish to save.  When you save it, the update does not reflect parameter  
changes.  The problem is that the save routine includes this check and  
it is associated with the parameter editor which is going to be closed.

To fix this, should pull the check for dirty out of the parameter  
editor so that the save gets associated with the new parameter editor  
created after the save.

